# npm publish allowlist is `files` in package.json (dist, template, README, SKILL, LICENSE).
# This file keeps dev-only artifacts out of the tarball belt-and-braces.
#
# NOTE on the template's own dotfiles: npm STRIPS certain dotfiles from a published
# tarball regardless of this file — a nested `template/.gitignore` (always dropped),
# `template/.npmrc` (registry-auth hygiene), and `.env*`-matched files. They therefore
# ship under NON-dotfile shim names (`gitignore`, `npmrc`, `env.example`, plus
# `github/` for `.github/`) that survive pack; src/scaffold.ts renames them to the real
# dotfiles at scaffold time (DOTFILE_RENAMES). scripts/build.mjs guards both halves.
node_modules
*.tsbuildinfo
.DS_Store
*.log
src
test
scripts
biome.json
vitest.config.ts
tsconfig.json
.npmrc
